1	//! The `squash-push` subcommand: squash the working copy into its
2	//! parent, advance a bookmark, and push — capture a repo's trailing
3	//! writes and publish them in one step.
4	//!
5	//! - Built for the bot's `.claude` bot repo, whose working copy
6	//!   accumulates session data continuously (the session tail); also
7	//!   useful on the work repo as a deliberate amend-and-push (a
8	//!   published-history rewrite, so the push is a forced update).
9	//! - Runs fully in-process: preflight validations, then squash +
10	//!   bookmark-set + push. A failure is a visible non-zero exit
11	//!   (the retired 0.69.0-2 predecessor delegated to a detached
12	//!   child that a sandboxed run silently killed — the loss
13	//!   diagnosed in 0.68.1).
14	//! - Reports an at-rest publish mismatch (BOOKMARK not matching
15	//!   `BOOKMARK@origin` — an earlier publish was lost) and proceeds:
16	//!   publishing is the command's job, so healing is not
17	//!   auto-fixing. Suppressed when run as push's `squash-push-bot`
18	//!   stage, where the mismatch is the normal mid-push state.
